fr.reflexe.viewshell.api.data

Interface ICell

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ITranslated

    public interface ICell
extends ITranslated
    Defines a prototype for typed data field, such as a relational database column.

    Cells may be fixed (such as a database column, where the existence is known in advance and a data value - possibly null - is always available), optional (known in advance but not necessarily always available) or dynamic (not known in advance and not necessarily always available).

    Generally, cells are provided by instances of ISource; they can also be provided via embedded arrays.

    Data for cells are primarily provided via items (which are primarily provided directly by sources).

    Thread safety: implementations are required to be safe for concurrent access.

    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    REFLEXE Technologies
    See Also:
    ICellStructure.getFixedCells(), ICellStructure.getOptionalCells(), IDataStructure.getExtraCells()

      • isGenerated

        boolean isGenerated()
        Indicates if the data in the cell is generated automatically.

        This implies in some (but not all) cases that the data is read-only. When creating new items, it may be null (which implies that the value is generated when storing the item, after the user has provided other values).

        It is not necessary for this property to be true for default values: it is intended to identified generated values for identity and auditing (such as marking primary keys, timestamps, and so forth).

        Returns:
        true if the value is always generated, otherwise false.
        Since:
        1.0
